Following up from the security audit finding about missing rate limiting on auth endpoints.

Proposed implementation:
- Token bucket algorithm
- 100 requests/minute per IP for public endpoints
- 1000 requests/minute per API key for authenticated endpoints
- Redis-backed for distributed counting

This is tagged as a critical fix so I'd like to get it into the next sprint.

Omar

