Content-Type: text/plain; charset=utf-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 7bit

Team,

Post-mortem for the October 3 payment processing outage:

**Duration:** 47 minutes (14:23 - 15:10 UTC)
**Impact:** ~230 failed transactions, affecting 18 customers
**Root Cause:** Memory leak in the payment webhook handler — a new regex pattern was compiling on every request instead of once at import.

**Resolution:** Hot-fixed by pre-compiling the regex. Deployed at 15:08 UTC, all services recovered by 15:10 UTC.

**Action Items:**
1. Add memory usage alerts (Lucas)
2. Add regex compilation to our code review checklist (Raj)
3. Retry failed transactions and notify affected customers (Maria)

Aisha

