Content-Type: text/plain; charset=utf-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 7bit

Current backup setup:

- Full backup: daily at 2am UTC
- Incremental: every 6 hours
- Retention: 30 days for daily, 7 days for incremental
- Storage: CloudStride S3-compatible object storage

With our data growth (about 50GB/month), we should probably move to continuous WAL archiving. It'll give us point-in-time recovery instead of snapshot-based.

Thoughts?

Lucas

